cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.NA, cs.QI. 

The paper discusses spectral analysis of matrix scaling and operator scaling, which are problems related to linear algebra and optimization. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the spectral gap condition, which is a concept from spectral graph theory, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another possible sub-category. The use of gradient descent algorithms and quantum expanders suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.QI (Quantum Physics) as additional likely sub-categories.
